    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>In order to capture planet formation features such as stratified
grain settlement, horizontal (radial and azimuthal) distributions
of grain sizes, and substructures, we propose to image three extended
protoplanetary disks (CI Tau, DL Tau, and HL Tau) at Band 7 and 6
with the highest angular resolutions.  Our CARMA data show that
particularly these three targets are largely extended.  In addition,
they appear to have a thinner and less flared disk than the hydrostatic
equilibrium case by our detailed modeling in Bayesian inference,
which implies that they have experienced grain settlement.  Moreover,
we detected hints of substructures toward all three targets. ALMA
will provide unprecedented datasets of at least an order higher
signal-to-noise and a factor of two higher angular resolution than
our current data.  The data and our modeling technique will offer
a unique opportunity to investigate dust properties and to find
substructures developed at this early protoplanetary disk stage.
To achieve our science goals, as well as continuum, we will obtain
13CO and C18O line data, which will provide gas distributions and
kinematic information needed for interpreting the substructures.</prp:abstract>
